==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|es|en}} {{term|sombrero||hat|lang=es}}, from {{term|sombra||shadow, shade|lang=es}} + {{term|-ero|lang=es}}, literally, "shade-maker."

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Sombrero (PSF).png|thumb|sombrero]]

# A [[hat]] of a particular kind, with a high conical or cylindrical crown and a saucer-shaped brim, highly embroidered, made of plush felt.
# A mixed drink with [[tequila]], named after the hat.

